CSE.html:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<html>
    <head>
        <title>CSE_GCET</title>
        <style>
            body,p,a{
                background-color:green;
                text-decoration: solid;
                color:yellow;
            }
        </style>
        </head>
        <body>
            <p>The Department of Computer Science and Engineering was established in the year 2005 and currently the department offers an Under Graduate program B.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering with an annual intake of 240 students and 1 Post-Graduate program M.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering with an annual intake of 30 students
                In continuation to the existing Course - B.Tech (Computer Science and Engineering) GCET has been approved with 4 new courses as - B.Tech programme in 
                <li><ol>"Computer Science and Engineering - Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning" (CSE-AI&ML) with an intake of 60.</ol>
                    <ol>"Computer Science and Engineering - Data Science" (CSE-DS) with an intake of 60.</ol>
                    <ol>"Computer Science and Engineering - Cyber Security" (CSE-CS) with an intake of 60.</ol>
                    <ol>"Computer Science and Engineering - Internet of Things" (CSE-IOT) with an intake of 60.</ol></li> 
                        from academic year 2020-2021.
                "Computer Science and Engineering - Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning" (CSE-AI&ML) has increased with an intake of 180 from academic year 2021-22.
                The Department is Headed by Dr. A. Sri Lakshmi is having a total experience of 21 years in Teaching and Research. Accomplished career demonstrating consistent success as an administrator and educator at the graduate and post-graduate education levels. 
                She is an effective communicator with excellent planning, organizational, and negotiation strengths as well as the ability to lead, reach consensus, establish goals and attain results.
                There are 10 Professors, 17 Associate Professors, and 82 Assistant Professors and 15 doctorates in the department. The department has a Programmer and 5 System Administrators to assist and maintain the computer laboratories. 
                All the faculty members are encouraged to participate in Faculty Development Programmes, Conferences, Workshops, Publication of Research Papers and active involvement in R & D activity.
            </p>
            <a href="https://zollege.in/courses/bachelor-of-technology-btech-computer-science-and-engineering">DETAILS</a>
            <img src="https://www.cit.edu.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/cse_img.jpg",width="500",height="500"/><br>
        </body>
</html>

<html>
    <head>
        <title>IT_GCET</title>
        <style>
            body,p,a{
                background-color:green;
                text-decoration: solid;
                color:rgb(255, 251, 0);
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>One of the rapidly growing technologies, Information Technology is 
           playing a deliberate role in every organization and alights its foot in every 
           walk of our life which also drives to meet emerging technology in the present and future era.
           This branch also enlightens students with all necessary technical and practical 
           knowledge required by the software industry. Also imparts training for placements which
           makes the students also to fulfil it for higher studies. Department of Information Technology 
           has been restarted in the year 2019 with an intake of 60 students. 
           The Department has highly committed faculty who graduated from various reputed institutions. 
           The IT Program was earlier accredited by NBA, New Delhi before it was discontinued. Department is headed by
            Dr.K.Srinivas has 20 years of experience in teaching. The Department has one Professor, two Associate Professors and four Assistant Professors. 
            The faculty is well experienced and is into research, which allows us to drive students to a correct path of education. 
            It has well-equipped laboratories to impart practical training and good practice to students and has strong external linkages with Industry, R&D establishments etc.
        </p>
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64,",width="500",height="500"/>

        <body>
           <p>The Department of Civil Engineering started functioning from the year 
              2014 with a B. Tech program of 120 students. The department is equipped
              with state of art laboratory facilities in the areas of Structural Engineering, 
              Transportation Engineering, Geotechnical Engineering, Environmental Engineering, 
              Engineering Geology, Surveying, Hydraulics and Hydraulics Machinery. 
              In addition the department has soft core labs in Pavement Analysis and Design, 
              Geographic Information Systems. The department is also equipped with library in 
              addition to a central library, with several volumes, titleos including e journals and print journals.
              The department is presently headed by Dr. R. Prasanna Kumar, Who has more than 
              25 years of teaching experience, 10 years of research experience.</p>
